# .taurignore — files excluded from the Tauri dev watcher (won't trigger a rebuild)
# See: https://tauri.app/reference/cli/#dev
#
# The agent (IronClaw) can write arbitrary files to the backend directory when
# workspace_mode=unrestricted and the user hasn't configured a custom workspace root.
# Without this file, any agent-created file would trigger a cargo rebuild and crash
# the running app in dev mode.
#
# Only .rs files and cargo manifests should trigger a rebuild.

# Ignore everything by default, then re-include Rust source
*
!src/
!src/**
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!build.rs
!.taurignore
